Package: iNEXT
Type: Package
Title: Interpolation and Extrapolation for Species Diversity
Version: 2.0.7
Date: 2016-01-18
Author: T. C. Hsieh, K. H. Ma and Anne Chao
Description: The package provides simple functions to compute and plot two types (sample-size- and coverage-based) rarefaction and extrapolation of species diversity (Hill numbers) for individual-based (abundance) data or sampling-unit-based (incidence) data.
License: GPL (>= 3)
URL: http://chao.stat.nthu.edu.tw/blog/software-download/
Maintainer: T. C. Hsieh <euler96@gmail.com>
Depends:
    R (>= 2.14)
Imports:
    stats,
    graphics,
    ggplot2
BugReports: https://github.com/JohnsonHsieh/iNEXT/issues
LazyLoad: yes
